  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Technology-enabled Open Schools for All</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This 3-year project, with a total amount of USD 3 million, aims to support Egypt, Ethiopia and Ghana to design, pilot test, and scale up Technology-enabled Open School Systems (TOSS) that can connect school based and home based learning to ensure the continuity and quality of learning no matter under normal or crises situations. Activities will include building national platforms and development of online content ; enhancing school and household connectivity; deploying relevant applications, and provision of training on digital skills. Priorities will be given to the most vulnerable groups including female teachers and students, children from rural areas, learners with disabilities.</narrative>
  </description>
